  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN187.1-kilavi"><app><lem>pirivuṇarttiya tōḻikkut talaimakaḷ colliyatu</lem><rdg wit="#C2 #C3 #C9v">talaimakaṉ piriviṉkaṭ ṭalaimakaṭkut tōḻi collitu</rdg><rdg wit="#RK">talaimakaṉ piriviṉkaṭ ṭalaimakaṭkut tōḻi colliyatūumām</rdg></app>.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">What SHE said to the confidante who informed [her] of the separation.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="AN187.1">
        <l>koḷpulam pakalat tuñci nammoṭu</l>
        <l>nāḷpala nīṭiya karantuṟai puṇarcci</l>
        <l>nāṇuṭai maiyi ṉīṅki cēynāṭ</l>
        <l>ṭarumporuḷ <supplied>va</supplied>litta neñcamō ṭēki</l>
        <l>nammu<supplied>ya</supplied>r puḷḷiṉ kātalar kaṟuttōr</l>
        <l>temmuṉai citaitta kaṭumparip puravi</l>
        <l>vārkaḻaṟ polinta vaṉkaṇ maḻavar</l>
        <l>pūntoṭai viḻaviṉ ṟalainā ḷaṉṉa</l>
        <l>tarumaṇaṉ ñe<supplied>mi</supplied>riya tirunakar muṟṟam</l>
        <l>pulampuṟuṅ kollō tōḻi cēynāṭ</l>
        <l>ṭalantalai ñemaiyat tāḷi lāṅkaṭ</l>
        <l>kalaicēr pirunta cilkuṭip pā<supplied>k</supplied>kat</l>
        <l>tel<supplied>vi</supplied>run tayara vēmat talki</l>
        <l>maṉaiyuṟai kōḻi yaṇaṟṟā<supplied>ḻ</supplied> vaṉṉa</l>
        <l>kavaiyoṇ ṭaḷira karuṅkāl <supplied>yāa</supplied>ttu</l>
        <l>vēṉil vaippiṟ kāṉaṅ kāya</l>
        <l>muṉaiyeḻun tōṭiya keṭunāṭ ṭāriṭaip</l>
        <l>paṉaiveḷi ṟarunta paiṅkaṇ yāṉai</l>
        <l>yoṇcuṭar mutirā viḷaṅkukati ramaiyattuk</l>
        <l>kaṇpaṭu pāyaṟ kaiyoṭuṅ kacainilai</l>
        <l>vāḷvāyc cuṟaviṉ paṉittu<supplied>ṟai</supplied> nīn<supplied>ti</supplied></l>
        <l>nāḷvēṭ ṭeḻunta nayaṉil paratavar</l>
        <l>vai<supplied>ku</supplied>kaṭa lampiyiṟ ṟōṉṟu</l>
        <l>maipaṭu māmalai vilaṅkiya curaṉē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>When, after having slept with us so that the loneliness, that gripped [us], departed, (1)</l>
        <l>he leaves, because of having [a sense of] shame, (3a-c)</l>
        <l>the secret union that had extended over many days, (2)</l>
        <l>goes, with [his] heart that is hardened [by the desire] for wealth difficult [to make] of distant lands, (3df.)</l>
        <l>[and] thinks of our promotion, [our] lover, (5a-c)</l>
        <l>like the first day of the flower arrow festival (8)</l>
        <l>for strong warriors who sport large anklets (7)</l>
        <l>with fast-moving horses who laid waste to the hostile frontier of the enemies, (5df.)</l>
        <l>will the courtyard of the brilliant mansion, spread with sand that was brought, (9)</l>
        <l>feel lonely, friend, – (10a-c)</l>
        <l>staying with pleasure while they prepare the night feast (13)</l>
        <l>in the village with little homes that sits close to the rocks, (12)</l>
        <l>in that place devoid of men, with Ñemai trees whose heads have suffered, in distant lands (10df.)</l>
        <l>on difficult ways through lost lands where the frontier has risen [and] run, (17)</l>
        <l>while the forest grows hot in the region of summer, (16)</l>
        <l>with black-trunked Yāam trees that have forked, bright sprouts (15)</l>
        <l>like the hanging dewlaps of the fowl residing by the house, (14)</l>
        <l>[going] to the desert blocked by cloud-covered large mountains, (24)</l>
        <l>where the green-eyed elephants, in order to eat the soft [part] of the palmyra, (18)</l>
        <l>appear like boats in the sea kept (23)</l>
        <l>by ruthless fishermen who rise for the daily hunt, (22)</l>
        <l>passing the dewy ghat for swordfish, (21)</l>
        <l>in a resting position, restrained by the hand on the bed when sleeping (20)</l>
        <l>on the occasion of shining rays when the bright glow [of the sun] is not [yet] mature? (19)</l>
      </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
